I think this picture says it all 😫
The finish line photo from the Montane Cheviot Goat last weekend! 
58 miles over 4100m of ascent in one of the most remote areas of England. 
It was hard! Very hard! conditions were brutal and I’ve never run through so many bogs 🤣
Wasn’t my day running wise, I felt like I was stuck in second gear most of the day
maybe that has something to do with all the crazy races and efforts I’ve done this year 😂 
The main thing is i enjoyed it and I made the most of a very special day in a very special place (I did do a fair bit of moaning to be honest 😂) 
This is a truly spectacular race and will definitely test even the most seasoned of runner. 
Go give it a crack I promise you won’t be disappointed 👌🏻
Thanks to Drew and the guys from @coldbrewevents for putting on a beautifully brutal race 😍❤️🙌🏻
#cheviotgoatultra #cheviotgoat #montanecheviotgoat #montane2022 #montane

I’ve had a few things rattling round my head lately, not too much mind as I’m not too clever 😂
I wonder how many tattooers now don’t use foot switches or clip cords?!?
I wonder if using metal grips and tips is going to slowly fade out so we won’t need to know the importance of sterilising tubes! 
I also wonder how many apprentices out there don’t even know what an ultrasonic or autoclave is!!? 
And the last one is a biggie in my opinion… I wonder with so many so called custom tattooers out there now only using iPads, how many of them can actually draw?!?? I don’t mean copy and paste an image and trace I mean actually draw with pencil and paper! 
This isn’t a post that’s meant to cause any beef so chill out!!! It’s a mere observation that has led to these questions! 
Please feel free to comment or let me know your thoughts! 
Happy 2023 tatters 🙌🏻
📸@gilly_photography

With less than a week until I tackle my longest point to point race yet @thenortherntraverse I’m starting to ask myself if I’ve done enough, am I strong enough?!?! 
My honest answer is no! 
I didn’t have the best start to the year with injury and I’m still not 100% sure if I’m totally on top of it! 
The only thing I know for certain is I’ll show up and give it everything I’ve got because at the end of the day that’s all we can do! I’d rather fail trying than not try at all. 
Looking forward to seeing everyone on the start line 🙌🏻
Stats for the race- 
300 kilometres 
6500m elevation gain

Had to take a few days to let this one sink in. My first DNF! 
Not something any runner really wants to have to do but after racing hard for well over 100 miles my calf decided to blow up! 
I really wanted to carry on but in all honesty that would have been a huge mistake. Things like this will happen and injuries are inevitable especially when your pushing hard.
I’ll be back stronger but for now now I just need to rest! 
Huge congratulations to my buddy @jamesnobles91 on another fantastic win it was a pleasure running with you for so long. 
Congratulations to everyone who toed the line finishing or not… top effort 👏🏻
Thanks to Shane and his absolutely fantastic crew working @thenortherntraverse everyone I met along the way was so lovely and supportive! 
I’ll see you all next year to get the job finished 🙌🏻🏃‍♂️🙏

Took me few days to get around to this but at the weekend I raced the inaugural 7 valleys ultra 
Stats 110k nearly 4000m of vertical gain. 
Anyway I felt super strong going into the race and baring a little bit of tendinitis in the last week leading up the the race my training block had gone super well! 
I owe a lot of that to my very good friend and coach @garyhouse_ (he’s not just silly on instagram you know 😂) 
My plan was to go out with the front pack and not make any moves until the first big climb up Rossett pike 🏔️ 
once we began the climb I felt like I was making a gap but a runner on them super poles was pounding up the hill after me as we crested the mountain it was time to push the running to see what he had! 
After 10 minutes or so of running I glanced back, he was nowhere to be seen! Great news i thought! From then on I felt completely in control of the race. 
I pushed if I felt anyone was getting close to me, otherwise I just enjoyed a beautiful day of running (barring the few cramping episodes I had 🤦‍♂️) 
So happy to take Win 🥇 
thanks to @13valleysultra for putting on a fantastic race. 
Special thanks to @garyhouse_ for doing a cracking job of crewing me the whole day!
Thanks to @the_omm for the support 🙌🏻
And my wife @lisalazenby85 for constantly having my back ❤️
Goes without saying really but a huge well done to everyone that got the job done over the weekend 🙌🏻🙌🏻
📸 @marathonphotos
